    "Standardizing the data preparation pipeline is challenging in the library design because various student cognitive models utilize data with diverse content and formats.",
    "For example, CD handles interaction data ignoring timestamp, while KT handles sequential interaction data.",
    "Additionally, models may selectively utilize features such as relations, contexts, and other relevant data features.To address the aforementioned challenges, let us first clarify the workflow of data preparation, as shown in Fig. 5.",
